data.text:
NFF Hampshire Honor Society (2021)

FIFTH-YEAR (2020)

Season lost due to the COVID-19 pandemic.

SENIOR (2019) | Game-by-Game Stats

Got to prove what he could do when healthy, playing in every game while starting the last nine … second on the team with three sacks and four quarterback hurries … first sack went for a 4-yard loss against Colgate … also made a solo stop on 1st-and-goal at the 1 that led to Dartmouth denying the Raiders any points on the drive in a 38-3 victory … had a key QB hurry on fourth down at Penn that helped turn the ball over on downs during the 28-15 victory in the Ivy League opener … posted a tackle for a loss among his three stops in the 59-24 romp over Columbia … dropped a season-high six ball carriers at Harvard, making some of the game’s biggest plays in the process … twice he hurried the quarterback to throw third-down incompletions in the fourth quarter that led to a punt and a missed field goal attempt … his last stop against the Crimson came on fourth down at the Big Green 4 to give Dartmouth the ball back with one minute left, setting up the game-winning, 96-yard drive for a 9-6 victory on a 45-yard Hail Mary pass … continued to provide big plays the following week at Yankee Stadium, sacking the Princeton quarterback twice for a combined loss of 16 yards … the first came on the first play from a scrimmage, setting the tone for the 27-10 win over the ninth-ranked Tigers … recorded four tackles for the third straight game in the season finale at Brown, helping Dartmouth clinch its 19th Ivy League title in the 29-23 road triumph.

JUNIOR (2018)

Missed the season due to an injury.

SOPHOMORE (2017) | Game-by-Game Stats

Varsity debut came in season opener at Stetson, assisting on a tackle at the line of scrimmage … also played on the home turf against Columbia.

FRESHMAN (2016)

Played for the junior varsity against Middlebury and Norwich, providing three tackles against the latter.

HIGH SCHOOL

Second-team all-state selection as a senior … all-conference and all-area on the gridiron and all-conference in track … captained football and track as a senior … led team with six interceptions while earning All-West Suburban Silver honors … recorded 69 tackles for the 14-0 Class 7A state champion.
